## Enabling a Service

Load the ``debops-find-source`` skill before inspecting role defaults.
Load the ``debops-find-documentation`` skill to look up role variables.
Load the ``debops-manage-inventory`` skill for the full inventory model.
Load the ``debops-run-playbook`` skill when you need to run playbooks.

### 1. Find the role name

DebOps service roles are named `debops.<name>`. The service is enabled by
adding a host to `[debops_service_<name>]` in the inventory `hosts` or similar
file.

### 2. Add host to service group

In `ansible/inventory/hosts` (legacy) or `ansible/views/<view>/inventory/hosts` (modern):

```ini
[debops_service_nginx]
webserver1
```

Multiple hosts can be listed one per line.

### 3. Configure role variables

Create a YAML file in `group_vars/` or `host_vars/` named after the role prefix:

```yaml
# ansible/inventory/group_vars/all/nginx.yml
nginx_flavor: 'full'
nginx__deploy_state: 'present'
```

Variables use the role name as a prefix (e.g., `nginx__*`, `postfix__*`,
`sshd__*`). Load the ``debops-find-documentation`` skill to look up role
default variables. Some older roles might still use a single underscore as
a variable prefix.

### 4. Verify

Load the ``debops-run-playbook`` skill for full details. Always use
``debops check`` (dry-run with diff) by default and only use
``debops run`` when the user explicitly confirms.
